    <p><img src="http://www.ostraining.com/images/drupal/Re-using-Drupal-fields.jpg" width="200" height="200" alt="Re-using-Drupal-fields" style="float: right;" />Sometimes we're able to give really clear advice: "Do this!" or "Don't do that!"</p>
<p>This is not going to be one of those blog posts.</p>
<p>Drupal gives you the ability to re-use fields. If you have an "Image" field, you could choose to use that same field on every content type on your site.</p>
<p>However, it's not always clear whether re-using fields is a good idea. Sometimes it is, sometimes it isn't.</p>
<p>Here's an overview of the advantages and disadvantages to consider before re-using Drupal fields.</p><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/ostrainingdrupal/~4/cXse6XtbCFY" height="1" width="1"/>
